## Doppler

```{r doppler-non-negatived}
plot_reconstruction("doppler", one_sided$doppler, "non-negatived")
```

```{r doppler-unconstrained }
plot_reconstruction("doppler", unconstrained$doppler, "unconstrained")
```

The Doppler comparison is the clearest support diagnostic. When the true
signal crosses zero, the non-negatived fit cannot represent its negative portion by
construction. This is correct behavior under the specified prior, not a
numerical failure.
 
